# module: eng.sampling
# status: supported-promoted-table-artifact-seed; planned generators
# purpose: deterministic sample tables and design sweeps with units, constraints, seed policy, and reviewable metadata.
#
# Current implementation:
#   promoted CSV tables whose schema/source/binding is sample-like produce
#   typed_payload.sample_tables[] entries with sample count, case_id column,
#   numeric parameter ranges, duplicate case IDs, deterministic row-hash
#   previews, and source hash. Native grid/random/LHS generation is still
#   planned.
#
# Planned helper vocabulary:
#   grid sample
#   latin_hypercube
#   random sample with seed
#   sample manifest
#
# Review contract:
#   parameter schema, ranges, seed when generated, sample count, sample row
#   hashes or hash previews, source hash, and diagnostics for duplicate or
#   invalid case IDs.
#
# Non-goal:
#   random sampling without an explicit seed must not pass repro review.
